cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.CR, cs.PF 

This paper focuses on the energy demands of link aggregates commonly used in network connections, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses energy-efficient Ethernet interfaces and their energy models, which could be classified under systems and control (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a practical method to share the load that minimizes overall energy consumption, which could be considered as a cryptographic application (cs.CR) or a performance evaluation (cs.PF).
